            <div class="card shadow-sm border-0 mb-4">
              <div class="card-body p-5">
                <h3 class="mb-4 content-heading">Author Guidelines</h3>
                <p class="mb-3">
                  <ol class="mb-3" style="line-height: 1.8;">
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Scope and Originality</strong>
                      <br />
                      All submissions must present original, unpublished work that is not under consideration   elsewhere. Manuscripts must fall within the scope and objectives of the conference/journal.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Author Eligibility</strong>
                      <br />
                      Submissions are invited from academicians, researchers, industry professionals, research  scholars, and students. Student submissions are encouraged and may include faculty   co-authorship. No minimum publication experience is required, provided academic standards   are met.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Language Requirements</strong>
                      <br />
                      Manuscripts must be written in clear and grammatically correct English. Authors must use  American English, but consistency must be maintained throughout the paper.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Plagiarism Policy</strong>
                      <br />
                      All submissions will be screened using plagiarism detection software.
                      <ul style="margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <li>Maximum permissible similarity: 10% overall, excluding references.</li>
                        <li>Manuscripts exceeding the limit may be rejected or returned for revision.</li>
                      </ul>
                      Plagiarism in any form is strictly prohibited.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Peer Review Process</strong>
                      <br />
                      Each submission will undergo a peer review process. Decisions may include acceptance,   acceptance with revisions, or rejection. The decision of the reviewer's team is final and   binding.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Registration and Fees</strong>
                      <br />
                      For accepted papers, at least one author must register. Registration fees are mandatory and   non-refundable and must be paid within the stipulated deadline to ensure for presentation   of paper in the conference. Publication charges will be separately applicable.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Presentation and Attendance</strong>
                      <br />
                      For conferences, at least one registered author must present the paper. Failure to present  may result in removal from the final proceedings. Outside Mumbai authors may present   through online mode.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </p>
                <h3 class="mb-4 content-heading">Submission Guidelines</h3>
                <p class="mb-3">
                  <ol>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Manuscript Format</strong>
                      <ul style="margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <li>Font: Times New Roman</li>
                        <li>Font size:
                          <ul style="margin-top: 4px; margin-bottom: 4px;">
                            <li>Title: 14 pt (bold)</li>
                            <li>Headings: 12 pt (bold)</li>
                            <li>Body text: 10–11 pt</li>
                          </ul>
                        </li>
                        <li>Line spacing: 1.15</li>
                        <li>Margins: Standard (1 inch / 2.54 cm on all sides)</li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Length and File Size</strong>
                      <ul style="margin-top: 8px; margin-bottom: 8px;">
                        <li>Full paper length: 6000-8000 words (including references, tables, and figures)</li>
                        <li>Abstract length: 150–250 words</li>
                        <li>Keywords: 3–6</li>
                        <li>Maximum file size: 5 MB</li>
                      </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Figures and Tables</strong>
                      <br />
                      Figures and tables must be clearly labelled and numbered. Captions must be placed below figures and above tables. All figures must be of high resolution and embedded within the text.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-3">
                      <strong>Referencing and Citations</strong>
                      <br />
                      References must follow the APA Style (7th Edition). All cited works must be included in the reference list.
                    </li>
                  </ol>
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

